HEADWORD: Intelligential
<hw>In*tel`li*gen"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intelligentiel</ets>.]</ety> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the intelligence; exercising or
implying understanding; intellectual.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧With act
<xex>intelligential</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of unembodied mind;
incorporeal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Food alike those pure⟦br⟧
<qex>Intelligential</qex> substances require.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intelligentiary</ent>⟦br⟧
